   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-EMAIL-SURVEILLANCE (London) _ As the Clinton
administration formally enters the debate about law enforcement
surveillance in cyberspace, the British government is about to
enact a law that would give the authorities here broad powers to
intercept and decode e-mail messages and other communications
between companies, organizations and individual citizens. By Sarah
Lyall.
</P>
