   OBIT-COVERDELL _ Sen. Paul Coverdell, R-Ga., a congressional
workhorse who quickly ascended to a leadership post and served as
the Senate point man for longtime friend George W. Bush, died
Tuesday at 61.
</P>
<P>
   ARK-GOVERNOR-RESIDENCE (Little Rock, Ark.) _ Gov. Mike Huckabee,
temporarily out of the governor's manse while it undergoes much
needed renovation, has moved into a cozy little place out back: a
double-wide trailer. By David Firestone. &QL;
