   EMPLOYEE-ATTITUDE (Undated) _ Increasingly, employees are
testing the boundaries of the American work ethic as employers,
hammered by recruiting and training expenses and fearful that they
will be unable to fill job openings, make allowances for just about
every form of misconduct. Offenses like frequent tardiness or
absenteeism, apathy and even insubordination that would have
merited a pink slip a few years ago are now being shrugged off as
