 PERSONALS: Taste Treats 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
The age-old question of which sells more, potato chips or corn
chips, is answered in ``Just Curious, Jeeves'' (Ask Jeeves;
$16.95),  &UR; Jack Mingo  &LR; and  &UR; Erin Barrett &LR; 's book about questions
posed on the Net to the electronic oracle. Potato chips, hands
down. Lay's says that Americans eat 7 million pounds of them every
day.
</P>
<P>
   On the other hand,  &UR; Demi Moore &LR; 's favorite snack is a glass of
water, says Fitness magazine.
</P>
<P>
   And  &UR; Gwyneth Paltrow &LR; , who the New Weekly of Australia says
stays thin with yoga and chain-smoking, will be seen ballooning to
350 pounds in the forthcoming movie ``Shallow Hal.'' This latest
cinematic trick-of-the-month (a la ``Big Momma's House'' and ``The
Nutty Professor'') is accomplished with a fat suit and computer
magic. The movie is about a middle-age model-loving man who falls
in love with Paltrow, a fat woman.
</P>
<P>
   Which brings to mind the Venus'-flytrap  &UR; Andrew Demcak &LR;  bought
at Safeway. According to the instructions that came with the plant,
if he feeds it fatty foods, its traps and leaves will blacken and
fall off. If he feeds it low-calorie ``bugs: flies, centipedes and
earwigs,'' say the instructions, ``your plant will have a long,
healthy wife.'' He's thinking insects are essential for marital
success.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; CHER'S NEW GOAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Cher &LR; , 54-year-old mother of 31-year-old &UR; Chastity &LR;  and
23-year-old  &UR; Elijah Blue &LR; , told the New York Daily News that
 &UR; Sharon Stone &LR; 's adoption of a baby resulted in her looking into
adoption too. ``When I heard about Sharon, I knew what had been
missing in my life. She is so happy, and I am so envious.''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Cher Convention 2000, a two-day event in Chicago
honoring the singer-movie star-saleswoman-goth heroine, had karaoke
singers, look-alikes and sales of T-shirts, albums and geegaws, but
it didn't have Cher.
</P>
<P>
   The closest substitute was impersonator  &UR; Wayne Smith &LR; , who sang
both parts of the duet on ``I Got You Babe'' and wore a beaded pink
pantsuit made of gabardine, a fabric not usually associated with
Cher.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; CHARLES SAYS &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; HE'LL STAY SINGLE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   In a complaint responding to a Times of London story saying that
 &UR; Prince Charles  &LR; was thinking about marrying  &UR; Camilla Parker &LR; 
 &UR; Bowles &LR;  in Scotland _ where the church allows divorced people to
marry _ the prince's office wrote the Press Complaints Commission
that he has no intention of marrying again.
</P>
<P>
   ``Decisions like this are not taken lightly,'' said the letter.
``We have got to the end of our tether. . . . This is not just
about the Prince of Wales. He is concerned for the feelings of his
children, the children of Mrs. Parker Bowles, the memory of his
late wife, and his public role.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
