   _  &UR; Prince Ernst &LR; , writes  &UR; Ronn Robbins &LR; , is correctly Prince
Ernst of Hanover, descended from a royal line ``that provided
England's throne with  &UR; Georges I &LR;  through  &UR; IV &LR; ,  &UR; William IV  &LR; and
 &UR; Victoria &LR; .'' Incidentally, the item was about his public urination
at a world's fair. And not incidentally, ``cum deo,'' as written by
 &UR; Billy Wilder &LR;  on scripts, means ``with God.''
