 PERSONALS: Taste Treats 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle news
file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
The age-old question of which sells more, potato chips or corn
chips, is answered in ``Just Curious, Jeeves'' (Ask Jeeves;
$16.95),  &UR; Jack Mingo  &LR; and  &UR; Erin Barrett &LR; 's book about questions
posed on the Net to the electronic oracle. Potato chips, hands
down. Lay's says that Americans eat 7 million pounds of them every
day.
</P>
<P>
   On the other hand,  &UR; Demi Moore &LR; 's favorite snack is a glass of
water, says Fitness magazine.
</P>
<P>
   And  &UR; Gwyneth Paltrow &LR; , who the New Weekly of Australia says
stays thin with yoga and chain-smoking, will be seen ballooning to
350 pounds in the forthcoming movie ``Shallow Hal.'' This latest
cinematic trick-of-the-month (a la ``Big Momma's House'' and ``The
Nutty Professor'') is accomplished with a fat suit and computer
magic. The movie is about a middle-age model-loving man who falls
in love with Paltrow, a fat woman.
</P>
