<P>
   UN-CRITIC (Bethlehem, N.Y.) _ It has been more than two years
since Scott Ritter walked away from his job as chief of a U.N.
weapons inspection team in Iraq. Today, the former Marine, 39, is
worlds away from that life. Now campaigning against sanctions
because he believes Iraq is no longer a threat, Ritter recently
moved to upstate New York where the biggest decision he's recently
faced was what color to paint the living-room wall. By ALAN
WECHSLER.
</P>
<P>
   SMUGGLER-RELEASED (San Francisco) _ A federal judge has knocked
more than two years off a drug smuggler's sentence and sent him
home to Australia because U.S. customs agents who worked on his
case in San Francisco got cash bonuses from the government for drug
seizures. By BOB EGELKO.
</P>
