   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MONEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ When Vicente Fox won the Mexican
presidency, citizens who voted for him knew the place to celebrate
was at the feet of nation's capital's most famous landmark, the
Angel of Independence on Reforma Avenue. But investors knew better.
The real place to party in Mexico City was in the financial
district _ at the Bolsa Mexicana de Valores, the country's stock
exchange. By SHANNON BUGGS.
</P>
<P>
   SMALL-TOWN-BROKER (San Antonio) _ The Edward Jones securities
firm has 5,700 offices sprinkled throughout America's small towns,
suburbs and neighborhoods. Another 1,000 brokerages have sprouted
in Canadian and British towns. By BILL DAY.
</P>
