   TV-FOOTBALL (Pasadena, Calif.) _ By all accounts, the comic
Dennis Miller has been in intense training camp sessions with Al
Michaels and Hall of Fame quarterback Dan Fouts, ABC's new ``Monday
Night Football'' broadcast crew. Everyone involved with the
telecast insists that Miller is not there just to provide comic
relief. Rather, ``Dennis will give us an attitude,'' executive
producer Don Ohlmeyer says. By MARK McGUIRE.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-SUPREMES (San Antonio) _ Singer Mary Wilson, the only
other original Supreme on the planet besides Diana Ross, isn't an
I-told-you-so sort of person. Oh, her comments could be juicy right
about now as Ross' ill-fated, faux Supremes ``Return to Love'' tour
is being called the biggest flop of the summer. But Wilson is mum
on the subject. By HECTOR SALDANA.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-DOUG-SAHM (San Antonio) _ When Doug Saldana died in
November, he left a country album in the can. The 12-cut disc,
``The Return of Wayne Douglas,'' has been on and off of release
lists for months. The Tornado-label collection is finally hitting
the streets this week. By JIM BEAL Jr.
</P>
