SAN FRANCISCO _  SERVICE  _ A crisis is looming at Bay Area
restaurants. In a city where eating out is a way of life,
restaurateurs are struggling to find servers and line cooks. For
Northern California diners, that struggle translates to higher tabs
and poorer service. &HT;     By Robin Davis  
 c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; WAITER &LR;  _ If you've ever considered getting a job
waiting tables, there may be no time liked the present. The roaring
economy has drained the pool of restaurant workers, leaving owners
and managers struggling to fill positions (see related story,
 &UR; SERVICE &LR; ).
<P>
   Kitchen workers are hard to come by, but trained servers are
even more scarce. Think anyone can be a waiter? Think again. &QL; 
 &UR; By Robin Davis &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
