SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; POTPOURRI &LR;  _ Poor wine service in a restaurant can
help ruin an evening out. The whole experience can be a minefield
of strange wine names, off-the-scale prices and service that's
either too friendly and casual or too stuffy and condescending.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Gerald Boyd &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; TASTE &LR;  _ Taster's Choice column will return next
week.
</P>
</TEXT>
