<P>
   HIGH-TECH BOOM NEAR SANTA'S HOUSE
</P>
<P>
   BC-ECOM-UNLIKELY-TECH-BOOMTOWN-NYTSF _ Oulu, Finland, must rank
as one of the world's most improbable technology boomtowns. Except
for forests and lakes, there isn't much within 100 miles of Oulu.
The most notable town to the north is Rovaniemi, which has built
its economy on the assertion that it is the true home of Santa
Claus. Yet this town of 100,000 people is home to hundreds of
electronics companies. Driven in part by Nokia, the Helsinki
company that is the world's biggest manufacturer of mobile
telephones, Oulu thrives as a center for research on wireless data
communications. It also has also become a hotbed for Internet
start-ups. Find out why in this feature. By Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
