   RUN-ADKINS (Sacramento, Calif.) _ Feature on Derrick Adkins, who
won the men's 400-meter hurdles at the '96 Olympics in Atlanta but
whose ongoing battles with depression left him in no shape to
defend his title in Sydney. But now he is off his medication _ with
his doctor's approval _ and trying to qualify for the Olympic team.
By Jere Longman.
</P>
<P>
   TOUR-DE-FRANCE (Lausanne, France) _ The Tour de France swerved
into Switzerland on Wednesday to honor a higher power. The lords of
cycling, the International Cycling Union, awaited the race in
Lausanne, their seat. By Samuel Abt.
</P>
