<P>
   Type of trip: Seven-day cruise for two to Caribbean with
cheapest cabin available on midlevel ship, including airfare.
Best deal: www.expedia.com _ $1,676, inside cabin on Sea Princess,
leaves Fort Lauderdale, Fla.; ports include Jamaica, Cozumel.
www.travelocity.com _ $2,090, inside cabin on Holland Westerdam,
leaves Fort Lauderdale; ports include Puerto Rico, Bahamas.
www.travelscape.com _ Not available. Travel agent _ $2,336, inside
cabin on Royal Caribbean Monarch of the Seas, leaves San Juan,
P.R.; ports include St. Thomas, St. John, St. Lucia.
Time spent: www.expedia.com _ 34 minutes. www.travelocity.com _ 56
minutes. www.travelscape.com _ NA Travel agent _ 14 minutes on
phone, two calls.
Bonus points: www.expedia.com _ 20 cruise lines to choose from.
www.travelocity.com _ Easy to compare facilities and itineraries
for up to 10 cruises at once and book online. www.travelscape.com _
NA Travel agent _ Offered constructive opinions on itineraries and
cruise line services and amenities.
Glitches: www.expedia.com _ Sent me to other sites, which often
wouldn't allow online booking or would not quote prices for
specific dates; had to book air fare and cruise separately.
Sometimes, links wouldn't work. www.travelocity.com _ Only five
cruise lines among selection; site kept crashing or ending up in
dead ends, forcing me to start over. www.travelscape.com _ Took a
couple of minutes to figure out cruises weren't offered. Travel
agent _ NA
LAS VEGAS Type of trip: Three nights' stay for two in moderate
hotel, airfare, transfers.
Best deal: www.expedia.com _ $653, Stratosphere; $705, Excalibur.
www.travelocity.com _ $704, Excalibur. www.travelscape.com _ $536,
Stratosphere; $646, Luxor. Travel agent _ $563, Stratosphere; $657,
Luxor.
Time spent: www.expedia.com _ 24 minutes. www.travelocity.com _ 36
minutes. www.travelscape.com _ 18 minutes. Travel agent _ 13
minutes, one phone call.
Bonus points: www.expedia.com _ Offered 121 hotels, more than other
sites. www.travelocity.com _ Easy to navigate and to compare
packages. www.travelscape.com _ Easy to browse hotel/air packages.
Travel agent _ Explained locations of hotels _ and their good and
bad points _ as he went.
Glitches: www.expedia.com _ Vegas packages weren't offered for
dates I wanted to travel; had to book air and hotel separately;
site crashed in middle of search and couldn't be accessed again for
10 minutes. www.travelocity.com _ Offered just 31 hotels; crashed
while trying to book, making me start over. www.travelscape.com _
None. Travel agent _ NA
CANCUN, Mexico Type of trip: Six nights' stay for two in moderate
to low-end hotel, airfare, transfers.
Best deal: www.expedia.com _ $1,653, Holiday Inn Express.
www.travelocity.com _ $1,160, Costa Real. www.travelscape.com _
$1,408 Holiday Inn Express. Travel agent _ $1,296, Oasis Cancun.
Time spent: www.expedia.com _ 31 minutes. www.travelocity.com _ 32
minutes. www.travelscape.com _ 7 minutes. Travel agent _ 11
minutes, one phone call.
Bonus points: www.expedia.com _ 52 hotel choices, including some
that weren't available on other sites, especially in budget
categories. www.travelocity.com _ Easy to find and browse Cancun
packages for specific dates and price ranges. www.travelscape.com _
Cancun happened to be featured destination; packages popped up
fast. Travel agent _ Said he'd been to Cancun and suggested only
properties he would personally stay in.
Glitches: www.expedia.com _ Could not get a package; had to book
air and hotel separately. www.travelocity.com _ Inexplicably, once
tried to book me at an Orlando hotel with a similar name to one in
Mexico. Insurance was automatically added at an extra cost, though
you could remove it with one click. www.travelscape.com _ None.
Travel agent _ NA
</P>
