</P>
<P>
   plus a report about his new gig. also a box or sider: Iacocca
talks about the biz world today. (Owers, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   DOW _ Disappointed investors dumped the shares of Internet
stocks that failed to meet overly optimistic expectations for
second quarter results, sending all major stock averages lower
despite good news elsewhere in the market. ``It's the Super Bowl
syndrome,'' said John Eade, director of research at Argus Research
in New York. ``The reality never lives up to the hype.'' (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-UNION _ The pilot unions at Delta Air Lines' two regional
subsidiaries are seeking to merge with the carrier's main pilot
union. They say their members are at a disadvantage in pay and
career issues as separate entities, because the Delta union wants
tighter controls on the types of planes the subsidiaries fly.
(Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   REC-ROOM _ Dot.com companies that are trying to attract _ and
keep _ younger employees who grew up playing PlayStation and
Foosball are outfitting their offices with all manner of games and
entertainment. From built-in ``frisbee breaks'' to impromtu
ping-pong tournaments we talk to these fun junkies to find out if
this is any way to run a business. (Harris, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
