their hair platinum blond. (Coyle, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
10. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   DEALER _ She's standing at a blackjack table at The Mirage
Hotel, expertly dealing the cards and chatting with patrons. Her
name tag reads ``Nancy'' and ``Dayton, Ohio.'' ``They want
customers to know where we're from because it's an icebreaker,''
explains Nancy Potasky Stein, who's been a Las Vegas dealer for 16
years. ``It gives them a chance to say they're also from Dayton or
Columbus or Cincinnati.'' Dressed in tuxedo shirt and bow tie,
short black skirt and teal-and-black vest decorated with a palm
tree design, Stein has worked her way up to the top of a profession
that she labels both fun and exhausting. (Dayton Daily News) WITH
PHOTOS. MOVED.
</P>
