for a vice president, Gov. George W. Bush usually puts loyalty at
the top of the list. It is one of the main reasons Sen. John McCain
is not a likely choice. But more broadly, Bush puts an enormous
premium on that quality. He expects it from his staff and from
himself. By Frank Bruni.
