   INTERNET-MUSICIANS (Undated) _ For a growing number of
musicians, the Internet serves as an equal opportunity jukebox.
Even as the recording industry and artists like Metallica try to
stamp out the practice of distributing copyrighted music for free,
tens of thousands of aspiring rock stars _ with no recording
contract and some with no chance of being signed _ are happily
using MP3 technology to give their music away. By Amy Harmon.
</P>
