risk and uncertainties, the Clinton administration on Wednesday
assured Pacific Northwest lawmakers that the Snake River dams will
stand for at least a decade. By Douglas Jehl. (Summary from wires.)
</P>
<P>
   TAXES-POLITICS (Washington) _ In early January, Speaker Dennis
Hastert told the Republican leadership to abandon its effort to
pass a single, hugely expensive tax-cut package. Instead, he
ordered up a series of narrowly drawn tax measures that could rise
or fall not on their pricetags but on their political appeal. In
one sense his strategy has played out as well as he could have
hoped. But in another sense, his strategy has led nowhere. By
Richard W. Stevenson. News analysis.
</P>
