r f BC-GENPARTS-EARNINGS0720     07-19 0310
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GENPARTS-EARNINGS0720-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    4% gain by Genuine Parts hits target
 &HT;    By Peralte C. Paul
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA - Buoyed by strong sales across most of its divisions,
Atlanta-based Genuine Parts reported a 4 percent increase in
second-quarter earnings Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Net income in the quarter ended June 30 rose to $96.6 million,
or 55 cents a share, from $92.6 million, or 52 cents a share, a
year earlier. The results matched Wall Street's expectations.
</P>
<P>
   Revenue increased 6 percent to $2.1 billion.
</P>
<P>
   The company distributes automotive and industrial replacement
parts. It also supplies office products and manufactures electrical
equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Sales increased 10 percent in the office products group. They
rose 9 percent in the industrial parts group and 7 percent in the
electrical group.
</P>
<P>
   The auto parts group _ its largest segment _ grew 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Analyst Matthew T. Stover at Salomon Smith Barney said the soft
growth in the automotive parts division is indicative of the
industry.
</P>
<P>
   ``From an industry standard, it was a tough quarter,'' said
Stover, explaining that car parts are better made, reducing the
frequency of replacing them.
</P>
<P>
   Genuine Parts officials said they expect that earnings for the
year will meet analysts' forecast of $2.27 a share.
</P>
<P>
   ``We will be pushing hard to improve the sales picture in the
automotive parts group,'' said Chairman Larry Prince. ``Secondly,
we will continue our efforts toward improving our overall operating
margins with specific emphasis on our recent acquisitions.''
</P>
<P>
   To increase auto parts sales, the company will push its
e-commerce site that was launched in March, and begin a national
advertising campaign, said Jerry W. Nix, executive vice president
of finance.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
