<HEADLINE>
NEW WAVE HAWAIIAN RECIPES 

</HEADLINE>
 
 EDS: Accompanies TASTE-OFHAWAII 
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALAN'S ASIAN GUACAMOLE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Yields 4-5 cups &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 avocados, peeled, pitted and diced &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup diced onion &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons sake &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup sliced scallions, green part only &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons freshly squeezed lime juice &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons minced ginger &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon chopped cilantro &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon vegetable oil &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon chile sauce with garlic (available in the Asian
section of well-stocked supermarkets) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon Louisiana hot sauce or Tabasco, optional &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, combine avocados, onion, tomato, sake, scallions,
lime juice, ginger, cilantro, oil, chile sauce, hot sauce (if
using) and salt. Mix gently without mashing the avocado. Serve
immediately, or cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for up to
two days.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per tablespoon: 12 calories, 1 gram fat, 1
gram carbohydrates, trace protein, 0 cholesterol, 30 milligrams
sodium, 65 percent of calories from fat. _ Adapted from ``Alan
Wong's New Wave Luau,'' by Alan Wong with John Harrisson (Ten Speed
Press; $35) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BANANA MOUSSE WITH MAC' NUT CREAM &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   6 ripe bananas, unpeeled &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Nut cream: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup unsalted butter &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 cups sugar &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups coarsely chopped macadamia nuts &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup heavy cream &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Garnish: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup heavy cream &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon sugar &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 400 degrees. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Place the bananas on a baking sheet and bake in the oven until
they turn black and the skins split, about 10 minutes. Let cool a
little and then peel the bananas and puree in a food processor or
blender. Pour the banana puree into six 2-inch ramekins and
refrigerate for two hours.
</P>
<P>
   To prepare the Mac' Nut Cream, melt the butter in a saucepan,
add the sugar and macadamia nuts, and bring to a boil. Continue
boiling until the mixture turns a dark golden brown. Stir in the
cream and when incorporated, remove the pan from the heat and cool
to room temperature. When ready to serve, warm the Mac' Nut Cream
gently. For the garnish, whip the cream with the sugar until soft
peaks form.
</P>
<P>
   To serve, place a chilled banana mousse on each serving plate.
Top with the whipped cream and pour the warm nut cream around.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 915 calories, 63 grams fat, 93
grams carbohydrates, 5 grams protein, 117 milligrams cholesterol,
21 milligrams sodium, 61 percent of calories from fat. _ ``Roy's
Feasts From Hawaii'' by Roy Yamaguchi and John Harrisson (Ten Speed
Press; $29.95) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HIBACHI MISO CHICKEN WITH PEANUT BUTTER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Serves 16 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   5 pounds chicken thighs or skinless boneless chicken breasts &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Marinade: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup miso (fermented soybean paste, available in Asian
sections of supermarkets and health food stores) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup smooth peanut butter &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup soy sauce &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup sugar &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup beer &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons minced fresh ginger &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon minced garlic &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Combine marinade ingredients and marinate chicken overnight in
refrigerator. Grill for approximately 35 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving using thighs: 400 calories, 26
grams fat, 11 grams carbohydrates, 29 grams protein, 120 milligrams
cholesterol, 920 milligrams sodium, 59 percent of calories from
fat. _ ``Sam Choy's Cooking'' by Sam Choy (Mutual Publishing;
$35.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NINETIES POTATO SALAD &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Serves 18 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 pounds new red potatoes &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 cups shredded crabmeat &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup bay shrimps &QL;
</P>
<P>
   4 hard-boiled eggs, chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup fresh corn kernels &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup pitted medium black olives &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup sliced water chestnuts &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups chopped fresh spinach &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup minced Maui onion &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup minced celery &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup grated carrots &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 1/2 cups mayonnaise &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper to taste &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Cook potatoes in lightly salted boiling water until fork-tender.
Cool, then cut into eighths.
</P>
<P>
   In a large mixing bowl, toss all ingredients lightly to combine.
Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper, if necessary.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional information per serving: 330 calories, 26 grams
total fat, 4 grams saturated fat, 80 milligrams cholesterol, 400
milligrams sodium, 18 grams carbohydrate, 7 grams protein. _ ``Sam
Choy's Cooking'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MACADAMIA-CRUSTED RED SNAPPER WITH HAWAIIAN PESTO &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Hawaiian pesto: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup packed cilantro leaves &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped macadamias &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 ounces Parmesan cheese, grated &QL;
</P>
<P>
   6 scallions, chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons chopped fresh ginger &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons freshly squeezed lemon juice &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 clove garlic, chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon sesame oil &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon salt &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup macadamia oil &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Fish: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   4 (6-ounce) red snapper fillets &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly ground pepper, to taste &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup all-purpose flour &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 eggs, beaten &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup finely chopped macadamias &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons macadamia or peanut oil &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For the Hawaiian pesto: In the bowl of a food processor, combine
cilantro, macadamias, Parmesan, scallions, ginger, lemon juice,
garlic, sesame oil and salt. Process until smooth. With motor
running, add oil in a thin stream until all is incorporated. Set
aside.
</P>
<P>
   Season fillets with salt and pepper. Dredge fillets in flour,
then dip in egg. Press macadamias onto each side. In a large
skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add the crusted fillets
and cook for about two minutes per side. Keep warm until all
fillets are cooked. Drizzle with Hawaiian pesto and serve
immediately.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 861 calories, 67 grams fat, 18
grams carbohydrates, 49 grams protein, 162 milligrams cholesterol,
775 milligrams sodium, 70 percent of calories from fat. ``_ The
Mauna Loa Macadamia Cooking Treasury'' by Leslie Mansfield
(Celestial Arts; $19.95) &QL;
</P>
