 PERSONALS: Many Varieties on Bush Family Tree 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
The hottest Bush of all, says Elle magazine, which has an eye for
beauty, is  &UR; George Prescott &LR;   &UR; Bush &LR; . This 24-year-old hunk, nephew
of presidential candidate  &UR; George W. &LR; , was ``my little brown one''
in 1988, when his grandfather introduced him to the public.
</P>
<P>
   George P. works as a paralegal and plans to enter law school in
the fall, but he meanwhile helps out in his uncle's campaign, says
Elle, where Bushites realize his `` &UR; Ricky Martin &LR;  appeal gives his
white-bread clan a touch of ethnic chic.''
</P>
<P>
   The magazine says that George P. is well aware of his sex appeal
and ``uses his Lothario looks to open doors once closed to Bushes _
witness Vanity Fair's Oscar party, where he drooled over
 &UR; Salma Hayek &LR; .''
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm looking for a balance,'' he says, ``between working hard
and succeeding and just having fun. I need that.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; Parties of the First Part &LR;
</P>
<P>
   At last week's Judiciary Committee hearing on Napster, Sen.
 &UR; Patrick Leahy &LR; , D-Vt., recalled that his ``beloved Grateful Dead
allowed anyone to tape their live shows and then trade tapes,
without ever demanding a nickel for the rights,'' reports Roll
Call.
</P>
<P>
   Sen.  &UR; Orrin Hatch &LR; , R-Utah, didn't have anything to say about
that precedent, but he wasn't going to let the Dems wear the sole
Deadhead crown. ``I like the Grateful Dead, too,'' he said, ``but
I'm not a slavish devotee.''
</P>
