   &QL; 
 &UR; LUXURY HANDBAGS &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; FROM ITALIAN PRISONS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A line of  &UR; Giorgio Armani &LR;  purses that sell for about $240 each
are being manufactured by inmates at the San Vittore prison in
Milan, says the Sunday Mirror of London. The workers are paid a few
dollars each.
</P>
<P>
   The handbags, display at Fashion Week in Milan, ``are official
Giorgio Armani products and are sold as part of our Armani Jeans
label,'' a spokesman for Armani told the paper. ``The aim is to get
the prisoners used to working again. Some have been inside a long
time.''
</P>
<P>
   Many of the prisoners are Mafia members serving life terms.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
