<P>
   SAKS-SPLIT (Undated) _ The answer to the question of whether a
country peasant can marry a Park Avenue swell and live happily ever
after appears to be no. Saks Inc., the owner of such regional
department stores as Proffitt's, McRae's and Parisan, announced
late Wednesday that less than two years after it acquired Saks
Fifth Avenue, its board of directors had approved a plan to split
again into two separate public companies. By Leslie Kaufman.
</P>
