   TRAVEL-JERUSALEM-HOTELS (Jerusalem) _ Jerusalem is not an
ordinary city and this is not an ordinary guide to hotels there.
William Orme Jr. makes discerning recommendations in a 3,000-word
piece full of details about decor, history, service and discounts.
The hotels visited included: the Olive Tree, a Holy Land theme inn;
the American Colony, an 84-room compound developed from a
19th-century pasha's manse; and the King David, which for true
self-indulgence, he concludes, is Jerusalem's best luxury hotel. He
