tourists for almost 40 years and unless President Clinton changes
his mind, the ban on United States tourist travel to Cuba is likely
to be tightened this summer. Meanwhile, travel from the United
States to Cuba increases. Edwin McDowell reports that there are
charters from New York, Miami and Los Angeles for exchange groups
and entrepreneurs take American tourists to Cuba without running
afoul of U.S. authorities.
