confident competitor. The main entrance of the Tsingtao brewery; the
German-style barrel is one of several German-style touches in the
factory. (Mark Landler/The New York Times)  *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) HILTON HEAD, S.C. -- July 19, 2000 -- BUSH-LOYALTY --
When he talks about his criteria for a vice president, Gov. George W.
Bush usually puts loyalty at the top of the list. Bush  puts an
enormous premium on that quality and expects it from his staff and
from himself. Bush, right, with Donald L. Evans, chairman of Bush's
presidential campaign and Karen P. Hughes, Bush's communications
director in during a campaign stop in February. (Andrea Mohin/The New
York Times) *LITE
</P>
