on selecting new windows. If you decide to buy  one, you will need
three measurements before you can place the order: the rough opening,
the outside dimensions and the thickness of the wall. To find the
rough opening, pry off the interior casing, then measure the
distance between the studs on either side of the window and the
distance between the rough sill and the header. (Ed Lipinski/New York
Times Illustration)
